      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Former Kiwi SURREAL MORAN NZ (1) made a winning start in Queensland when he raced parked from a much wider barrier and beat a promising juvenile for a narrow win at Albion Park last week. That was his first outing for close to seven weeks and he should be better for it. Draws to enjoy the favours so could go on with it. FITZROY NZ (4) has been competitive of late and kept the ball rolling last time when a 5 metre fourth behind some smart three-year-olds at Albion Park. A repeat of that performance should stack up well here. KASH FUND (2) can play a role again after he led from this barrier and kept going for a last-start win by 5.7 metres at Albion Park. BENNYDASOOK (8) deserves respect having come from this barrier to place in his last two outings.",
